date-released: 2026-05-28
version: "1.0"
abstract: >
  ESF (External Signal Fabric) is an architectural pattern for the layer
  that fuses customer-external state — markets, logistics, geopolitics,
  supplier health, weather, commodity — with customer-internal state
  surfaced by the Progressive Discovery Spine (PDS), producing a single
  decision substrate that the Adversarial Coordination Spine (ACS) can
  reason over. ESF is a peer to PDS, not subordinate; ACS pulls from
  both. The pattern addresses four documented failure modes of naive
  external-signal integration: signal pollution, stale-signal
  commitments, provenance gaps, and the commodity trap (raw signals
  without fusion produce no moat). The pattern is defined as ten
  principles plus reference SLAs and a numbered build sequence.
